where ⊗ is the matrix Kronecker product. We have included a simple example to illustrate the concepts. The corresponding design (D) and extended design matrices (D ⊗ Q) for the aforementioned example are shown in Fig. 6b. The design matrix includes an intercept term for all the samples and an increment for the tumor sample. If this experiment only studied gene expression, the contrast matrix would simply test if the increment of expression in the tumor samples is different from zero. The Kronecker product is equivalent to replacing each of the entries of matrix D, by matrix Q multiplied by the corresponding entry in D. Given this, the proposed linear model is:6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
